data.title: CH-406 Course Outline:: Petroleum Refining & Petrochemicals, CH-406 BSIC Spring Semester VIII
data.meta_description: CH-406 Course Outline:: Petroleum Refining & Petrochemicals, CH-406 BSIC Spring Semester VIII - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document outlines the course CH-406 on petroleum refining and petrochemicals. It covers topics including the origin and formation of petroleum, crude oil evaluation, petroleum processing techniques, and the production of various petrochemicals. The course literature includes books and articles on petroleum refining technology, petrochemical processes, and oil and gas exploration and production. Key concepts covered include crude oil composition, classification, properties, evaluation of physical characteristics, distillation processes, and the production of petrochemicals such as methanol, ethylene, propylene, and BTX compounds.
